properties.FacilityDescription:
Overview

Clear Creek Campground offers a great setting to enjoy active water sports at Sardis Lake. Five million visitors head to the lake each year for boating, swimming and fishing. The Sardis Nature Trail is a popular attraction at the base of the dam.

Natural Features:

Sardis Lake covers over 98,000 acres in the rolling hills of northwest Mississippi. The man-made lake sits on the Tallahatchie River at an approximate elevation of 400 feet. The campground is forested with bottomland hardwoods.

Recreation:

Sardis Lake offers an array of recreational activities, including fishing, boating, water skiing and swimming. A scenic trail near the campground offers great hiking and biking opportunities.

While the campground is not directly on the water, it is within a short drive to a swimming beach and boat ramp.

Facilities:

Clear Creeks 52 sites have electric hookups and some are equipped with water hookups. Flush toilets, showers and drinking water are provided. Younger campers love the parks playground.

Nearby Attractions:

The John W. Kyle State Park, across the lake from Clear Creek, offers a swimming pool, golf course and recreation hall. Just east of Sardis Lake is Holly Springs National Forest, where wildlife viewing is a popular activity.
properties.FacilityDirections: From Oxford, Mississippi, take Highway 314 north 8 miles and follow signs to the campground.
